node.text:
That’s right… the 3rd Annual Fxck Cancer Charity Golf Invitational is a go for 2021!
This year, we’re bringing the much anticipated event to the Strawberry Farms Golf Club in Irvine, CA on Wednesday, October 6th.  Registration is now open just use the link in our bio, get your foursome together and register ASAP… this event always sells out quick!
Special thanks to all our incredible sponsors that help make this event the huge success that it is and to all our supporters🙌🏼.
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #golfcharityevent #golf #charity #FCThrowbackThursday

node.text: Implemented in 2011, Dyin 2 Live Dreams is a wish-granting program committed to helping those who are currently in the fight against cancer by giving them a one-of-a-kind “VIP Experience” that may be a source of hope, joy, and inspiration while they continue in their fight against these terrible diseases. Through our extensive network of friends, supporters, and partners, we put together our VIP Experiences, focusing on select music festivals, concerts, and sporting events throughout the year. We take our Dyin 2 Live Dreams recipients backstage and behind the scenes at these events to meet their favorite bands, artists, athletes, and celebrities. Meet-and-greets, signings, watching their favorite bands side stage, backstage access, media interviews, photo ops, and more are all apart of the VIP Experience! Our Dyin 2 Live Dreams recipients walk away from the experience with the will and determination to continue in their fight against cancer. We want to show them that life is worth fighting for and that no one fights alone.

node.text:
#FCThrowbackThursday featuring our friend and supporter Laura and family celebrating her brother Chiza’s heavenly birthday back in April🙏🏽🤍. #NoOneFightsAlone when is comes to cancer and this was his support system throwing punches along side him throughout his battle🙏🏽. We love this photo and along with this family we keep Chiza in our hearts 🙏🏽.

Who do you fight for?- yourself, a loved one, a friend? Who ever it is give a 🤍 in the comments below for them and some love to our girl Laura and her family.

Thank you for sharing your photos with us, we love seeing them and especially sharing them with our #fxckcancercommunity . Please continue to send them in to us so we can share your light with others who may be in a dark place.🙏🏽
.
.
.
#FCThrowitUpThursday #FCTogetherWeFight #TogetherWeFightThursday #tbt 
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER 

Thank you so much for the shirt❤ I recieved it Saturday and yesterday we celebrated my brother's 44th birthday, his 1st heavenly birthday away from us and it was perfect❤❤

node.text:
#FCWarriorWednesday and today we ask everyone to rally around our fighter Stephanie as she goes to battle with stage 4 triple negative breast cancer🙏🏽. #NoOneFightsAlone in our #fxckcancerfamily so please send her all your positive prayers and words of encouragement to let her know we are all in her corner to help lift her spirits and help her get through this 🙌🏼. Stephanie cancer may be tough but you are tougher!! You got this warrior #KEEPFIGHTING. Please leave all your love for Stephanie in the comments below

“Chemo #4 and no more hair ☹️ so I had to put on my big girl pants and fight like a warrior today and not let myself get depressed as shaving my head this time was harder than previous times . But here’s to kicking cancers ass !!! And my @fxckcancer shirt is fitting for today #fuckcancer🖕#tnbc”
.
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #triplenevativebreastcancer

node.text:
We love seeing our #FxckCancerfamily representing with tattoos to permanently show how they feel about cancer and for those that have been impacted.  Whether it’s for themselves, a friend or a loved one, we all can relate. Today we thank Brian Anderson for his permanent support for his friend who is fighting stage 4 lung Cancer and who as pictured started off this tattoo for him🙌🏼. #NoOneFightsAlone and it’s friends and support systems like Brian that our fighters pull strength from to continue in their battle and to beat cancer🙏🏽. 

We thank you Brian for allowing us to share these photos and your friend is in our prayers, we hope to share his survivor story very soon🙏🏽. 
Please leave love for our friend Brian in the comments below and be sure to tag us in your #FxckCancerTattoo photos for a repost.
#TogetherWeFight
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #tattoo

#FCMerchMonday RESTOCK ALERT✨ Back in stock in all sizes we have our #FCfam favorite Fighters club and Survivor tee as well as our vertically stacked FC mens and women size tees back in our warehouse.  Don’t forget to sign up for our FC Newsletter to stay up to date on all other restocks and to also receive your lifetime 10% discount code🙌🏼. 

Thank you for proudly representing our #fxckcancer gear and in our mission of early detection and prevention🙌🏼. We also know that when others in the fight see our #FXCKCANCER gear they know they are not alone in their battle and feel supported by our #FCfamily 🙏🏽🤍

node.text:
#FCSurvivorSunday We can’t express enough how much we love sharing your survivor stories and to champion all your victories🙏🏽🙌🏼. Today we celebrate our warrior Leela beating endometrial cancer 🙌🏼🎉. Leela we love your positive attitude and how you advocate for early detection in hopes to help others avoid and prevent cancer. Keep smiling and keep shining and know that we will always be in your corner cheering you on🤍💯. Please leave love for our girl Leela in the comments below.

“I finished my treatments on August 26 2020 and had my CT scan on September 16, 2020. Today, I saw my oncologist and she said there is no evidence of the disease. I know it can come back, but today I am free of cancer and calling that a win. Today i’m saying Fuck Cancer”
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #survivor

node.text:
#FCSurvivorSaturday today we celebrate and champion young warrior Nathan who bravely fought & BEAT CANCER👏🏼! Stories like Nate’s make our day & we know that sharing journeys like his will give other fighters the hope & inspiration that they too will be able to share their survivor story with us one day🙌🏼. Nathan you are a true warrior & we are so honored to share your positivity & fighting spirit with our #fxckcancercommunity . You have made an impact on us all & you are destined for greatness 🙌🏼. Please leave love for Nate in the comments below, here is his story told by his sister Emily.

“On October 14, 2020 Nathan was taken to the hospital for back pain. They ran a bunch of x-rays & couldn’t find anything wrong with his back. My mom kept pushing the doctors to run more tests, finally they agreed to a blood test. Once the results came in they misdiagnosed Nate with leukemia. The doctors at the hospital told us they couldn’t do anything for him & sent us to Children’s Hospital Los Angeles for further testing. Once he arrived they tested him further & found traces of cancer cells called rhabdomyosarcoma in his body. They also told us that his back was in so much pain because he had 2 compressed fractures. Nate was at the hospital for about 20 days because he was getting tests done & the port incision would not heal. Throughout the span of his treatment they were never able to locate where the cancer actually lurked (they are assuming it’s in his bone marrow since they can’t find it anywhere else). He went through all 40 weeks of treatment with his usual smile on his face and kept his faith that he was going to be okay because “God only puts his strongest soldiers through the toughest battles.” Fast forward to the beginning of July, Nate was eligible to undergo an experimental treatment to try to get rid of any cancer cells that the 40 week chemo didn’t kill. The treatment is usually only for patients who have leukemia & it’s been done to one person with rhabdomyosarcoma in Europe. Nathan is the first in the USA to get this treatment done for his type of cancer. Yesterday he finally got to come home from that treatment and he is officially CANCER FREE 🥳”

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Fuck Cancer on August 06, 2021 tagging @moira.horan. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Today we say #FxckCancer for warrior Moira Horan & want to surround her in prayer & positivity while she goes toe to toe with cancer for a second time around 🙏🏽🤍. Moira you are a fighter & have such a strong will & mindset there’s no doubt in our hearts that you will get through this & show cancer you are not one to be messed with! You are in our thoughts and prayers and we are sending you strength to help you along your battle. We ask that everyone please send words of encouragement & love for our girl in the comments below. #NoOneFightsAlone

“Everything happens for a reason.
Four weeks ago yesterday I set out on a 6 hour ride with my dear friend Ran, as part of my training for Ironman Lake Placid, my 13th full distance Ironman. Not sure if I should consider 13 as lucky or unlucky. An hour into the ride we were in Long Branch & turned to the ocean, something I’ve done more times than I can count. I’m not quite sure what happened but one minute I was enjoying the beautiful day & the next minute I was on my back on the ground. Ran wanted to call my husband, I said call 911. Fast forward to the emergency room – turned out I had an open fracture in my left wrist which required surgery & apparently any surgery requires a routine chest X-ray.
On Friday morning the surgeon came back to fill me in on my surgery (a 15 cm plate & 10 screws) & he mentioned he saw something on my lung. Since I had a history of cancer he suggested I follow up promptly with my doctors at Sloan Kettering. I did that the same day. Fast forward through lots of tests, turns out my cancer is back. Recurrent. In my lung & in my lymph nodes and some other “suspicious” spots.
I’ve still got lots to work out & my medical team is very positive they can arrest this. I’m getting a port on Tuesday. Chemotherapy treatment starts maybe the end of July. A long haul that could go through the end of April.
So, send prayers and good wishes. TNBC sucks. Thank you God & my mom for shoving me into that barricade. I still have no symptoms.”

#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #fxckcancerfriday

That’s right… the 3rd Annual Fxck Cancer Charity Golf Invitational is a go for 2021!
This year, we’re bringing the much anticipated event to the Strawberry Farms Golf Club in Irvine, CA on Wednesday, October 6th.  Registration is now open just use the link in our bio, get your foursome together and register ASAP… this event always sells out quick!
Special thanks to all our incredible sponsors that help make this event the huge success that it is and to all our supporters🙌🏼.
.
.

node.text:
It’s #FCWarriorWednesday and today we rally around our fighter Ang in support and positivity as she takes on cancer💪🏽. Ang you are a total badass and we thank you so much for sharing your strength and positive mindset with us all🙌🏼. You are truly an inspiration and we know that other warriors in your shoes will find so much encouragement and motivation from reading your story and how you choose not only how to fight cancer but how to LIVE while doing it! We are all in your corner championing you Ang, cancer didn’t know but it just started a fight we know you are going to finish and come out on top of! Please send our warrior Ang love and words of encouragement in the comments below, here is her story:

“My name is Ang (@goodrunning26.2) and I was diagnosed with stage 3b invasive ductal carcinoma (breast cancer, hormone negative, HER2+) in January 2021. No genetic markers. 
.
I went through 5 months of TCHP chemo. Had a double mastectomy with no reconstruction. 95% response to chemo but the residual invaded through the chest wall with positive surgical margins. Currently undergoing radiation. And then 10 months of Kadcyla chemo. 
.
I am an avid runner and ran throughout chemo. It was tough but I am tougher. Training for marathon number 14 this fall while in active treatment. Exercise is supposed to help reduce side effects and I’ve read it can even help improve outcomes. So I make it a priority to stay physically active and support it with sleep and nutrition for recovery.
.
One thing that helps me keep a positive mindset is making a long list of fun stuff I want to do and then making future plans and making them happen. Some big goals but also lots of little things that bring me joy. I don’t want to just focus my energy on not dying of cancer. I want to make the most of actually LIVING.  #fxckcancer 👊”
.
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #warrior #fighter

node.text:
Today’s #FCTattooTuesday is a dedication piece done for beautiful wife by her loving husband. As we all know #NoOneFightsAlone when it comes to cancer and our loved ones are always right there in our corners swinging punches along side their warriors in the fight. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Since being diagnosed with ovarian cancer Candace Flores has become a big supporter of our page and the uplifting stories shared by other warriors that have walked in her shoes. Her husband Noe then went and permanently had his support for her in her fight tattooed on him to show cancer exactly how we feel about it🖕🏼. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Candace know that you have this entire #fxckcancerfamily in your corner as you fight and we are all sending you positivity and prayers that you kick cancers ass! Stay strong, stay positive and #KEEPFIGHTING ! You got this💪🏽! We hope to share your survivor story very soon🙏🏽. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Please leave love for our warrior Candace and her loving husband in the comments below.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

HUGE CONGRATS TO @janie_gopackgo @jshandcraftedusa for winning these support bundles 🙌🏼🙌🏼 we thank everyone for all your support and for all the tags! Fir our winners please direct message us with your shirt size and mailing addresses and again congrats!⭐️#FCMerchMonday Attention all cancer warriors, supporters & fighters it’s a GIVE AWAY ALERT⭐️
We thank you for all your continued love and support, we can’t express how grateful we are to share such an amazing community with you all and together we are making a difference🙌🏼. Through the stories all our warriors bravely share it’s providing so much hope, encouragement, inspiration and motivation for others in their battle with cancer to #KEEPFIGHTING! 
We thank all of our warriors for sharing your journeys you are the true heroes! As a thank you for all your support we want to give 2 special winners a support package of FC goods🤍. Here’s how you can win ⬇️

1️⃣. Like and SHARE this post with the arrow icon on the bottom left corner with your friends and family. Be sure to tag us @fxckcancer #fxckcancer so we see it🤍
2️⃣. Tag your friend or loved one that you want to also win this bundle in the comments below and be sure to follow us @fxckcancer (Unlimited entries)
3️⃣. Stay tuned, winner will be announced on this post tomorrow 8.3.21
.
.
.

.

It’s #FCSurvivorSunday and we can’t tell you how much messages like this one from our friend, fighter, warrior and survivor Ray Camacho means you us🙏🏽🙌🏼. Ray you are a champion and you are a true inspiration. Your strength, bravery and courage are unmatched and we thank you for sharing your light with us all🙌🏼. Know that you will always have us in your corner as well as the entire #fxckcancercommunity 💯. Thank you for keeping us posted and huge congrats warrior!!Please leave love for our man Ray in the comments below 🤍
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“Hey guys I just finished up my last radiation treatment about a week ago !! Got my back surgery today and on the road to recovery baby❤️❤️❤️You guys helped me so much and gave me inspiration everyday!!! I’m so thankful for everything you guys have done!!!! You truly make sure no one fights alone and it is so amazing !!! Sending so much love and thanks to you all!!!!!!!! THANK YOUUU!!!!!” ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
